17
00:00:32,800 --> 00:00:33,400
Hi guys.

18
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:35,000
I'm Qiao Yiyu from Gen1es.

19
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:36,160
(Qiao Yiyu, member of Gen1es)

20
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:37,240
Today we're watching

21
00:00:37,240 --> 00:00:38,400
Ep 5 of Live and Love S2.

22
00:00:38,780 --> 00:00:39,600
Can't wait for this.

23
00:00:39,600 --> 00:00:40,080
Yeah.

24
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:40,480
Come on.

25
00:00:40,480 --> 00:00:41,520
Let's begin.

26
00:00:41,520 --> 00:00:41,880
Alright.

27
00:00:41,880 --> 00:00:42,880
(Getting to the point)

28
00:00:42,880 --> 00:00:44,120
Islanders,

29
00:00:44,920 --> 00:00:47,160
all the women staying on the island

30
00:00:47,210 --> 00:00:49,480
will get to compete again.

31
00:00:49,480 --> 00:00:51,120
The winner

32
00:00:51,120 --> 00:00:53,040
will receive a Relay Date Card.

33
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:54,800
(Swap Date Card)
They compete daily.

34
00:00:55,440 --> 00:00:57,080
What is this?

35
00:00:57,480 --> 00:00:59,440
Here are the rules for this round.

36
00:00:59,440 --> 00:01:01,720
Four islanders start at the line

37
00:01:01,920 --> 00:01:02,960
holding a palm-leaf fan

38
00:01:02,960 --> 00:01:05,600
and fan the toy piglet
into the target box.

39
00:01:05,600 --> 00:01:06,640
That counts as a win.

40
00:01:06,640 --> 00:01:08,040
Give it your all, babe.

41
00:01:08,040 --> 00:01:09,240
Why is it a piglet?

42
00:01:09,300 --> 00:01:10,420
(Here comes your piggy~)

43
00:01:10,660 --> 00:01:11,980
(I got you)

44
00:01:12,440 --> 00:01:13,240
Start.

45
00:01:13,840 --> 00:01:14,400
Fan the piglet.

46
00:01:14,400 --> 00:01:15,540
(Interesting)
This is hard.

47
00:01:18,840 --> 00:01:20,920
Can I just kick it straight in?

48
00:01:21,100 --> 00:01:22,240
(Kid, you play without honor)

49
00:01:22,240 --> 00:01:22,640
Too much.

50
00:01:22,880 --> 00:01:23,500
(Immersed)
How?

51
00:01:23,500 --> 00:01:24,580
(Curious)
This is tricky.

52
00:01:24,660 --> 00:01:27,460
(Worried)

53
00:01:27,480 --> 00:01:28,560
I made it.

54
00:01:28,760 --> 00:01:29,200
Chen Yijia.

55
00:01:29,720 --> 00:01:30,800
(Chen Yijia wins)
Congrats.

56
00:01:30,980 --> 00:01:32,660
(Hey~ not bad!)

57
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:35,240
Who came up with this game?

58
00:01:35,240 --> 00:01:38,460
("Top-tier game". I'm impressed!)

59
00:01:38,520 --> 00:01:40,200
My piglet counts as in, right?

60
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:41,400
A date won from the piggy game.

61
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:42,480
Winner of round two.

62
00:01:42,480 --> 00:01:43,440
(New to me!)
Wu Yihan.

63
00:01:43,440 --> 00:01:45,800
Congrats to Wu Yihan
on winning a date card.

64
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:47,480
Wu Yihan wants to date Zhang Zizheng.

65
00:01:47,660 --> 00:01:48,640
(Guessing)

66
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:49,040
Yeah.

67
00:01:49,040 --> 00:01:49,760
The two of them...

68
00:01:49,760 --> 00:01:51,080
She asked out his former partner.

69
00:01:51,080 --> 00:01:52,080
Chen Yijia...

70
00:01:52,080 --> 00:01:53,360
(Thinking)

71
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:54,600
It used to be Zhang Zizheng.

72
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:55,600
Now it's Yang Tianyu.

73
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:58,480
Attention, islanders.

74
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:01,600
Congrats on Chen Yijia and Yang Tianyu.

75
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:03,240
You can go on a date.

76
00:02:04,340 --> 00:02:06,460
(Unbelievable. Processing)

77
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:07,080
Swap.

78
00:02:07,080 --> 00:02:08,100
I don't quite get it.

79
00:02:08,100 --> 00:02:08,690
(Emotional hit)

80
00:02:08,690 --> 00:02:09,990
(Spectator zone)
Emotional hit.

81
00:02:09,990 --> 00:02:10,760
He's upset.

82
00:02:11,280 --> 00:02:13,640
I really liked her the moment I saw her.

83
00:02:13,640 --> 00:02:14,280
I'm shocked.

84
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:16,680
(Shocked)
Then why is her reaction to me so...

85
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:17,640
Impossible to read.

86
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:19,640
(Don't try to guess a girl's thoughts)

87
00:02:19,640 --> 00:02:22,400
Congrats on Wu Yihan and Zhang Zizheng.

88
00:02:22,400 --> 00:02:24,400
You can go on a date.

89
00:02:24,420 --> 00:02:25,400
(Expanding new horizons)

90
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:26,240
Date swap.

91
00:02:28,880 --> 00:02:30,360
His feelings are written

92
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,280
all over his face.

93
00:02:31,280 --> 00:02:34,620
(Laughing. Upset.)

94
00:02:37,600 --> 00:02:38,960
Exactly what I was thinking.

95
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:40,280
The prophet has arrived.

96
00:02:40,560 --> 00:02:42,440
He's about to lose it.

97
00:02:42,440 --> 00:02:43,480
He's completely losing it.

98
00:02:43,900 --> 00:02:45,160
(Focused)
This is so dramatic.

99
00:02:45,220 --> 00:02:46,740
(Don't mention it)

100
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:49,520
So were you into Yijia from the start?

101
00:02:49,540 --> 00:02:50,280
(Asking bluntly)

102
00:02:50,280 --> 00:02:50,840
That's direct.

103
00:02:50,840 --> 00:02:51,880
That direct, huh?

104
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:52,840
She might be

105
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:55,400
a bit more eye-catching to me
than other girls.

106
00:02:55,820 --> 00:02:57,120
(Holding back the words)

107
00:02:57,120 --> 00:02:59,040
But when you showed up the next day...

108
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,720
I didn't mean I'd be playing around.

109
00:03:00,760 --> 00:03:01,800
That's pretty honest.

110
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:02,600
Because...

111
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:03,280
He is honest.

112
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:05,680
I'm not sure how to put it.

113
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:08,920
You're pretty appealing too.

114
00:03:08,920 --> 00:03:10,880
Honestly, after spending time with him,

115
00:03:10,880 --> 00:03:13,440
I could feel him getting closer

116
00:03:13,440 --> 00:03:14,000
to me.

117
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:14,720
She's happy.

118
00:03:14,720 --> 00:03:15,460
(I could tell)

119
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:18,040
And the timing for her is just perfect.

120
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:19,480
It just happens to be when...

121
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:21,000
(I get you)
He felt depressed.

122
00:03:21,000 --> 00:03:21,400
Yeah.

123
00:03:21,400 --> 00:03:22,680
When he was feeling a bit down.

124
00:03:22,920 --> 00:03:24,400
I think we can wait...

125
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:27,560
Like after Yijia

126
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:28,480
and Tianyu...

127
00:03:28,780 --> 00:03:29,680
After their date today,

128
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:31,400
she might have some new thoughts.

129
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:34,080
I think you could
spend more time with her.

130
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:36,080
You can ask her about it.

131
00:03:36,320 --> 00:03:37,960
I think she's very thoughtful.

132
00:03:37,960 --> 00:03:40,160
(Comfortably straightforward)
She knows Chen Yijia's situation.

133
00:03:40,160 --> 00:03:41,320
And she was basically

134
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:43,240
sharing her own thoughts

135
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:45,080
while still respecting the other person.

136
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:45,440
Right.

137
00:03:45,440 --> 00:03:46,400
She's genuine.

138
00:03:46,540 --> 00:03:48,160
(Honest is the key)
Her way of expression

139
00:03:48,160 --> 00:03:48,880
feels easy.

140
00:03:49,020 --> 00:03:51,020
(Let's keep watching for a bit)

141
00:03:51,040 --> 00:03:53,120
(Chen Yijia and Yang Tianyu on a date)
You mentioned

142
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:55,120
your votes all going to three guys.

143
00:03:55,680 --> 00:03:56,660
What do you mean by that?

144
00:03:56,660 --> 00:03:59,040
If I gave my votes
to three different guys...

145
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:00,600
But this date...

146
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:01,320
The pressure.

147
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:03,400
Can someone

148
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:05,560
be interested in that many at once?

149
00:04:06,560 --> 00:04:07,800
Feels pretty aggressive.

150
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:08,760
(Aggressive)
Well.

151
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:11,120
She's got that guarded vibe.

152
00:04:11,540 --> 00:04:12,660
(Guarded type)

153
00:04:12,700 --> 00:04:14,420
(Aggressive vs Defensive)

154
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:17,000
It's gotta be mutual attraction.

155
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:19,080
This clearly isn't going

156
00:04:19,120 --> 00:04:19,920
smoothly.

157
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:22,000
(My opinion)
Feels like an interrogation.

158
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:24,040
(I get you)
Two spies probed each other.

159
00:04:24,440 --> 00:04:25,640
Going back and forth.

160
00:04:26,240 --> 00:04:27,880
Feels kinda like she's avoiding something.

161
00:04:32,690 --> 00:04:33,920
(Subtle Vibe)
That's it?

162
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:34,840
Yeah.

163
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:36,760
(Feeling uneasy)
This part is uncomfortable.

164
00:04:36,920 --> 00:04:38,240
Do you think, in this show,

165
00:04:38,840 --> 00:04:41,000
is it more important to stay…

166
00:04:41,800 --> 00:04:43,720
or to find someone you genuinely like?

167
00:04:44,760 --> 00:04:46,360
If there's no one I genuinely like,

168
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:47,920
then staying is more important.

169
00:04:48,640 --> 00:04:49,440
Got it.

170
00:04:49,490 --> 00:04:50,530
(Probing)
Getting awkward.

171
00:04:50,530 --> 00:04:51,360
(Vibe)
That scene...

172
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:53,800
(Toe-curling level awkward)
I was embarrassed on her behalf.

173
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:56,080
I think it could be because…

174
00:04:56,080 --> 00:04:58,240
she just went through
that whole elimination thing.

175
00:04:58,240 --> 00:04:59,720
(Guessing)
She might feel stressed.

176
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:02,000
The competition rules played a part.

177
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:04,240
And she's hesitant to be too honest.

178
00:05:05,760 --> 00:05:07,800
Your main goal is to stay in the game.

179
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:09,080
Exactly.

180
00:05:09,920 --> 00:05:10,560
Take a breather.

181
00:05:10,560 --> 00:05:11,760
It's making me a bit tense.

182
00:05:11,760 --> 00:05:14,180
(Food therapy)

183
00:05:14,220 --> 00:05:16,380
(Pressure level off the charts)

184
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:19,140
I feel like she's...

185
00:05:19,140 --> 00:05:20,440
After going through elimination,

186
00:05:20,440 --> 00:05:22,720
she's really treating this like a game.

187
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:24,440
Feels like she's filming a talent show.

188
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:25,640
I mean it.

189
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:26,680
(Purely my view)
I feel

190
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:27,280
that...

191
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:28,880
she might be super career-driven.

192
00:05:29,320 --> 00:05:30,260
She's forming alliances.

193
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:31,560
(Survival battle)
She's not

194
00:05:31,560 --> 00:05:32,360
really bonding.

195
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:34,760
She's just trying to stay in the show.

196
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:35,640
Yeah.

197
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:37,120
("Survival battle")
But Yang Tianyu

198
00:05:37,120 --> 00:05:38,720
wants to have a genuine conversation.

199
00:05:39,320 --> 00:05:40,440
(Not same page)
So it's a bit...

200
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:41,280
But,

201
00:05:41,280 --> 00:05:43,560
I get why she has
that self-protection mode.

202
00:05:43,560 --> 00:05:45,840
Maybe right now she's in

203
00:05:45,840 --> 00:05:48,400
a pretty tense mental state.

204
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:49,840
(Tense)
She just tends to

205
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:51,880
double down on guarding herself.

206
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:53,040
Because

207
00:05:53,040 --> 00:05:54,960
before they get to know you,

208
00:05:54,960 --> 00:05:56,640
their curiosity doesn't always

209
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:58,160
have to be that strong

210
00:05:58,400 --> 00:05:59,840
for them to start engaging with you.

211
00:05:59,840 --> 00:06:01,200
I think it's a give-and-take.

212
00:06:01,240 --> 00:06:02,040
Yeah.

213
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:04,520
I'm actually super relaxed.

214
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:06,160
I cleared my mind today.

215
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:08,080
Because I didn't expect much.

216
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:10,000
No expectations about love?

217
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,480
Yes, in this show.

218
00:06:11,960 --> 00:06:13,460
Is this some kind of

219
00:06:13,460 --> 00:06:14,680
league of the disheartened?

220
00:06:14,680 --> 00:06:16,680
(League of the disheartened:
missed date edition)

221
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:17,720
So...

222
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:19,400
How was yesterday?

223
00:06:19,880 --> 00:06:20,840
How did you

224
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:21,960
vote for?

225
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:23,600
That's pretty direct.

226
00:06:23,600 --> 00:06:24,540
You're asking me this

227
00:06:24,540 --> 00:06:25,560
while we're on the swing.

228
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:30,000
You voted for me and others?

229
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:31,520
Be a bit more confident in yourself.

230
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:33,040
Okay?

231
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:37,640
They both don't need a date chance.

232
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:39,100
Feels like it's heating up.

233
00:06:39,440 --> 00:06:41,160
Maybe heating up too fast.

234
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:42,720
They're constantly going out.

235
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:44,690
(True love without date)
Making their own chances.

236
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:46,600
Is that Yang?

237
00:06:47,640 --> 00:06:48,400
Is that she?

238
00:06:48,620 --> 00:06:49,360
(Mood breaker)

239
00:06:49,360 --> 00:06:49,720
Yeah.

240
00:06:49,720 --> 00:06:50,840
Hello.

241
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:51,320
Hi.

242
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:52,360
Is this seat comfortable?

243
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:53,320
Yeah, it's nice.

244
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:55,220
Wanna have a seat?

245
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:57,520
She's actually sitting down.

246
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:58,920
You can try sitting for a bit.

247
00:06:59,360 --> 00:06:59,920
Here you go.

248
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:00,700
(Interesting)

249
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:02,720
This is so awkward.

250
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:04,640
(Feeling awkward for others again)
It is.

251
00:07:04,640 --> 00:07:05,200
Having fun?

252
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:06,240
Alright, let's sing then.

253
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:06,840
Go ahead, sit.

254
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:07,320
Wait.

255
00:07:08,320 --> 00:07:10,400
Shouldn't you sit beside them?

256
00:07:10,500 --> 00:07:11,720
(Another one?!)

257
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:13,600
We're singing.

258
00:07:14,880 --> 00:07:16,120
Way to cut the vibe completely.

259
00:07:17,560 --> 00:07:18,120
Here I am.

260
00:07:18,560 --> 00:07:18,920
Wow.

261
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:20,360
The weight.

262
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:22,120
Come join us.

263
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:23,000
Come on.

264
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:23,480
You could...

265
00:07:26,140 --> 00:07:30,700
(LOVE)

266
00:07:30,780 --> 00:07:31,620
(Absolutely)

267
00:07:31,620 --> 00:07:33,180
(Absolutely "god-tier")

268
00:07:33,180 --> 00:07:35,340
(Absolutely "god-tier" scene)

269
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:36,280
Good buddy.

270
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:36,640
Funny.

271
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:39,920
He just wrecked the date spot.

272
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:43,260
(I'll protect my buddy's happiness!)

273
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:44,880
(You can even pull this off?!)
Wow.

274
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:46,640
That worked perfectly.

275
00:07:46,640 --> 00:07:47,360
(Still processing)

276
00:07:47,360 --> 00:07:48,680
The swing is gone forever.

277
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:50,160
This is real awkward now.

278
00:07:51,920 --> 00:07:53,360
Has anyone thought about the swing?

279
00:07:53,900 --> 00:07:55,980
(Who's here to speak for me?)

280
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,000
So unbelievably boring.

281
00:07:57,000 --> 00:07:57,720
Yeah, hi.

282
00:07:58,120 --> 00:07:58,440
Hey.

283
00:07:58,520 --> 00:07:59,240
Here you are.

284
00:07:59,280 --> 00:08:00,280
Finally got a chance.

285
00:08:00,280 --> 00:08:00,940
(The show begins)

